I liked NW, but all it made me want to do is play D&amp;D for real again... so I did! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
By the way, dragons in BGII are easy as pie.<br>
You must either have a mage or be a mage, and you must have two things; the ablity to cast some sort of summoning spells, and the spell that removes magic resistance.<br>
Basically, you go into the dragon's room, surround him with your summoned creatures, and then cast your remove resistance spell. He'll then start attacking your creatures (he'll probably kill some, but just keep summoning more as they die). Make sure you have cast at least 3 of the resistance removing spells, then let him have it with direct damage spells, especially magic missle (sometimes not all the resistance will go away, but a few of the missles will hit). If you have more than one party member, you'll finish off the dragon in no time. <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Politics is supposed to be the second oldest profession. I have come to realize that it bears a very close resemblance to the first.&quot; -Unknown<br>
